<subSubSection pageId="271" pageNumber="876" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="271.[180,1386,289,836]" pageId="271" pageNumber="876">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,545,570,599]" pageId="271" pageNumber="876">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Sulawesi Montane Rat has a fairly wide distribution, butit is probably threatened by deforestation from logging and agricultural expansion. It is found in Lore Lindu National Park. Research is needed to fully understand its natural history, taxonomy, and conservation threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
